---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Get Started">
  <article>
    <h1>Get Started</h1>
    <p class="subtitle" style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--color-text-muted);">
      10 minutes to build the context that makes agents useful
    </p>

    <h2>The Context Interview</h2>

    <p>
      Before agents can help you, they need to understand you. This interview takes
      10 minutes and produces a <code>context.md</code> file — the foundation for all
      agent interactions.
    </p>

    <p>Answer naturally. Voice dictation works great. Raw honesty beats polished answers.</p>

    <h3>Part 1: Who You Are (2 min)</h3>
    <ul style="width: var(--content-width); padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <li><strong>What do you do for work?</strong> Role, industry, company size</li>
      <li><strong>What tools do you use daily?</strong> Software, platforms, devices</li>
      <li><strong>What languages do you work in?</strong> Speaking, writing, coding</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Part 2: What Hurts (3 min)</h3>
    <ul style="width: var(--content-width); padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <li><strong>What task do you dread most?</strong></li>
      <li><strong>When did you last lose significant time on something avoidable?</strong> Tell the story.</li>
      <li><strong>What information do you wish you had at your fingertips?</strong></li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Part 3: What Success Looks Like (2 min)</h3>
    <ul style="width: var(--content-width); padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <li><strong>If you could delegate one thing to an agent tomorrow, what?</strong></li>
      <li><strong>What does a great work morning look like?</strong> First 30 minutes.</li>
      <li><strong>What would change with a reliable assistant who knows your context?</strong></li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Part 4: Boundaries (1 min)</h3>
    <ul style="width: var(--content-width); padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <li><strong>What should an agent NEVER do for you?</strong></li>
      <li><strong>What information would you NOT share with AI?</strong></li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Part 5: Quick-Fire (2 min)</h3>
    <ul style="width: var(--content-width); padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      <li>Timezone</li>
      <li>Preferred output language</li>
      <li>Communication style (formal / casual / direct)</li>
      <li>Info format preference (bullets / narrative / visual)</li>
      <li>Biggest professional goal, next 6 months</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What Happens Next</h2>

    <p>Run this through Claude Code:</p>

    <pre><code>claude "Read my context interview and generate a context.md
that an agent can use to understand me. Be specific."</code></pre>

    <p>
      The output <code>context.md</code> becomes the foundation.
      Every agent reads it. Every suggestion is personalized.
      Disproportionate value from 10 minutes of honesty.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
